## Poker (Texas Hold'em — Player vs Dealer)

### Game stages
| Stage | Description | Community Cards |
|-------|-------------|-----------------|
| **Pre-flop** | 2 private cards dealt to each, first betting round | 0 |
| **Flop** | 3 community cards revealed, second betting round | 3 |
| **Turn** | 1 more card revealed, third betting round | 4 |
| **River** | Final card revealed, last betting round | 5 |
| **Showdown** | Hands compared, best hand wins | 5 |

---

### Player actions per round
| Action | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| **Bet** | Add credits to the pot |
| **Check** | Pass without betting (only if no one has bet yet) |
| **Fold** | Forfeit — lose all credits bet so far |

**Dealer strategy:** The dealer (machine) bets if holding ONE PAIR or better; otherwise checks.

---

### Hand rankings (lowest to highest)
| Rank | Hand | Example |
|------|------|---------|
| 1 | **High Card** | Highest card in hand |
| 2 | **One Pair** | Two cards of the same value |
| 3 | **Two Pair** | Two different pairs |
| 4 | **Three of a Kind** | Three cards of the same value |
| 5 | **Straight** | 5 consecutive cards |
| 6 | **Flush** | 5 cards of the same suit |
| 7 | **Full House** | Three of a Kind + Pair |
| 8 | **Four of a Kind** | Four cards of the same value |
| 9 | **Straight Flush** | Straight of the same suit |
| 10 | **Royal Flush** | A, K, Q, J, 10 of the same suit |

---

### Final hand formation
Each player uses the **best 5-card combination** from their 2 private cards and the 5 community cards (7 cards total).

> **Implementation note:** This requires evaluating all possible combinations of 5 from 7 cards — the most complex algorithm in the project. Planned for the final phase.

---

### Game flow
1. Player places initial bet (`/start`) — deducted from wallet immediately
2. 2 private cards dealt to player and dealer (dealer cards hidden)
3. **Pre-flop** → player bets, checks, or folds
4. **Flop** (`/flop`) → 3 community cards revealed → player bets, checks, or folds
5. **Turn** (`/turn`) → 1 card revealed → player bets, checks, or folds
6. **River** (`/river`) → final card revealed → player bets, checks, or folds
7. **Showdown** → dealer cards revealed, both hands evaluated, best hand wins

---

### Payouts
| Result | Payout |
|--------|--------|
| Win | Entire pot |
| Loss | Loses all credits bet |
| Fold | Loses credits bet up to that point |
| Tie | Pot is split evenly |
